data.title: Shining Victory (Original photograph from the 1941 film) by Irving Rapper (director); A.J. Cronin (playwright); Howard Koch, Anne Froelich as Anna Froelick (screenwriter); James Stephenson, Geraldine
data.meta_description: Warner Brothers, Burbank, CA - 1941 - Vintage reference photograph from the 1941 film. With manuscript ink annotation on the verso identifying actress Geraldine Fitzgerald. Based on the 1940 play, "Jupiter Laughs," by A.J. Cronin. A psychiatrist is hired to do research on a type of dementia. He falls in love with his lab assistant but when she suddenly dies in a lab fire, he quits his work to go live out her dream of doing missionary work in China. Set in London, England and Scotland. 8 x 10 inches. Very Good plus. - Shining Victory (Original photograph from the 1941 film)
